		<hr size="1">i was 2boxing my wiz and bard over the weekend and found it a pain to swap between the wiz and the bard to cast some spells. </P><P>i made a few macros, but would like some input from others with more knowledge about this stuff then my self.</P><P>bard = 29<BR>wiz = 34 (just dinged to 34 last night in MM at entrance camp)</P><P>bard is doing 90% of the work, just using wiz to snare and finish off the mob, as well as good back up to deal with overpulls.</P><P>macro 1 (FoB)<BR>/sit off<BR>/cast 1<BR>/pause (forget exact time, but i think its 40)<BR>/sit on</P><P>macro 2 (DD spell)<BR>/sit off<BR>/cast 2<BR>/pause (again forget exact time here)<BR>/sit on</P><P>those are about all i use other then /assist and currently have that set to just generic target so i can swap back and forth a bit faster.</P><P>i am hoping to move this pair into LGuk entrance <a href="http://eqatlas.com/uppergukmap.html">#7</a> on this map.  there are a pair of frogs at the bottom of the stairs.  if they are tank classes i can split them rather easy, but when they are caster class i have a pain dealing with them.</P><P>the new DD may help, but im not sure if that will or not.  any sujestions on adjusting macros, or spells?</P><P><hr><font style=font-size:8pt color=yellow>*Worlds worst speller*<BR><font color=yellow><BR>"For those who believe, then no proof is needed.  For those who are skeptics, then no proof will suffice."<font color=00FFFF><BR>"Pigs get fat, but Hogs get slaughtered and VI is a big HOG."<BR><font color=yellow> "So, reading some of my posts is sort of like having sex in your parents house???"  Dr. Zin</P><P></font><BR><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
